org.catacomb.druid.swing

Class TristateCheckBox.TristateDecorator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.catacomb.druid.swing.TristateCheckBox.TristateDecorator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.ItemSelectable, javax.swing.ButtonModel
    Enclosing class:
    TristateCheckBox

    private class TristateCheckBox.TristateDecorator
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.swing.ButtonModel
    Exactly which Design Pattern is this? Is it an Adapter, a Proxy or a Decorator? In this case, my vote lies with the Decorator, because we are extending functionality and "decorating" the original model with a more powerful model.

      • getState

        TristateCheckBox.State getState()
        The current state is embedded in the selection / armed state of the model. We return the SELECTED state when the checkbox is selected but not armed, DONT_CARE state when the checkbox is selected and armed (grey) and NOT_SELECTED when the checkbox is deselected.

      • nextState

        void nextState()
        We rotate between NOT_SELECTED, SELECTED and DONT_CARE.
